National_City.James M. Carter and Judith N. Keep Unite: The James M. Carter and Judith N. Keep United States Courthouse at 333 West Broadway in San Diego, California, is a sixteen-story federal courthouse facility on 2.6 acres (11,000 m2) that includes courtrooms, judges chambers, offices and courtroom galleries of the United States District Court for the Southern District of California, along with offices of the Internal Revenue Service and the General Services Administration. Construction was completed in 2012. When the building opened in March 2013 it was San Diego's third federal courthouse.
